    "content_hash": "e90b5ef0029710ae",
    "department": "Hardware",
    "description": "About Sesame\n\nSesame believes in a future where computers are lifelike - with the ability to see, hear, and collaborate with us in ways that feel natural and human. With this vision, we're designing a new kind of computer, focused on making voice agents part of our daily lives. Our team brings together founders from Oculus and Ubiquity6, alongside proven leaders from Meta, Google, and Apple, with deep expertise spanning hardware and software. Join us in shaping a future where computers truly come alive.\n\nAbout the Role\n\nIntegrating a complex sensing \u0026 computing system into a compact, attractive \u0026 functional wearable form factor requires significant mechanical expertise. The PDE must drive or influence all aspects of development, including system architecture, mechanical form/architecture, thermal design/test, component \u0026 vendor selection/evaluation, prototyping roadmaps and execution, along with test \u0026 calibration.\n\nThe ideal candidate has experience owning wearable electronics design, strong prototyping skills, knowledge of materials and fabrication, good aesthetics, exposure to image sensor and battery integration, and the ability to collaborate across domains.\n\nWe are a small team working on very ambitious projects. In a fast-paced startup, everyone must be comfortable, collaborative, decisive, and able to achieve results with limited supervision.\n\nInitial responsibilities: own mechanical architecture \u0026 design for all wearable hardware workstreams. Identify and onboard design and fabrication partners. Define and bring up the ME tool flow. Prioritize and drive explorations to solve integration challenges.\n\nResponsibilities:\n\n - Architect, design, simulate, prototype, and ship mechanical systems and components in wearable form factors.\n\n - Generate models, drawings, simulations, and specifications to support internal and external partners in the design and manufacture of mechanical components.\n\n - Mechanical subject-matter-expert supporting efficient collaboration with Electrical, Firmware, ID, and soft goods experts to solve complex integration problems.\n\n - Primary point of contact for identifying, evaluating,g and directing materials and fabrication partners.\n\n - Travel as needed for product or prototype development.\n\nRequired Qualifications:\n\n - 7+ years of relevant work experience with product design.\n\n - 4+ years of relevant work experience with wearable product design.\n\n - Experience with complex electromechanical integration, including sensors, cameras, batteries, antennas, and audio systems, in very small form factors.\n\n - Working knowledge of material properties, such as plastics, metals, adhesives, and glass.\n\n - Experience shipping products in a lead or principal engineer role.\n\n - Expert with Computer Aided Design (CAD) tools \u0026 mechanical simulation tools.\n\n - Knowledge of high-volume manufacturing techniques (stamping, machining, 3D printing, injection molding, etc).\n\n - BS or MS in ME or equivalent.\n\nPreferred Qualifications:\n\n - Master's degree in Mechanical Engineering.\n\n - 10+ years of experience in a consumer electronics company.\n\n - In-depth knowledge in one or more areas within Product Design.\n\n - Experience shipping wearable electronics with significant ID/Cosmetic constraints.\n\nSesame is committed to a workplace where everyone feels valued, respected, and empowered. We welcome all qualified applicants, embracing diversity in race, gender, identity, orientation, ability, and more. We provide reasonable accommodations for applicants with disabilities. Contact careers@sesame.com for assistance.\n\nFull-time Employee Benefits: \n\n - 401 (k) max employer match: 3.5% of compensation\n\n - 100% employer-paid health, vision, and dental benefits for you and your dependents\n\n - Unlimited PTO and sick time\n\n - Flexible spending account with employer matching up to $1,650/year (medical FSA)\n\n - Guardian Employee Assistance Program (EAP)\n\n - Opportunity to share in the company's success with competitive stock options\n\nBenefits do not apply to contingent/contract workers.",
    "employment_type": "FullTime",
